{"action": "patch", "name": "paragu-ai-builder", "old_string": "**ReferenceError trap:** Adding `${overlayColor || 'rgba(10,10,20,0.85)'}` to a JSX template literal but forgetting to add `overlayColor` to (a) the TypeScript Props interface AND (b) the component's destructuring params causes a runtime `ReferenceError: overlayColor is not defined` that crashes the ENTIRE section via the error boundary. Fix: always add new props to the interface AND destructuring block simultaneously. Test by checking `docker service logs paragu-ai-builder_web --tail 5 | grep \"ReferenceError\"` after deploy — if present, the fix is to patch both locations and redeploy.", "new_string": "**ReferenceError trap:** Adding `${overlayColor || 'rgba(10,10,20,0.85)'}` to a JSX template literal but forgetting to add `overlayColor` to (a) the TypeScript Props interface AND (b) the component's destructuring params causes a runtime `ReferenceError: overlayColor is not defined` that crashes the ENTIRE section via the error boundary. Fix: always add new props to the interface AND destructuring block simultaneously. Test by checking `docker service logs paragu-ai-builder_web --tail 5 | grep \"ReferenceError\"` after deploy — if present, the fix is to patch both locations and redeploy.

## [object Object] Link Bug — Nav Prefetch Creates Phantom 404s

When a standalone client's nav links contain PAB paths (`/s/en/nexa-paraguay/programas`), the header component must strip the prefix BEFORE the `<Link>` is rendered. If the stripping is done correctly but Next.js's `<Link>` prefetcher munges the path (e.g. `/sobre` returns 200 but the prefetcher emits `/sobre?_rsc=3lb4g 404`), the console shows `[object Object] 404` errors.

**Root cause series of mistakes:**
1. `href` in the content JSON is `/s/en/nexa-paraguay/programas` (PAB path)
2. The header does `"/" + n.href` → `"//s/en/nexa-paraguay/programas"` (double slash)
3. Next.js renders the `<Link href="//s/en/nexa-paraguay/programas">` as `[object Object]`
4. The prefetcher tries `/[object%20Object]` → 404

**Fix in TWO places (desktop AND mobile nav):**
```tsx
{items.map((n: any, i: number) => {
  const href = (n.href || n.path || "").replace("/s/en/nexa-paraguay", "") || "/"
  return (
    <Link key={i} href={href} className="...">
      {n.label}
    </Link>
  )
})}
```
The `.replace()` must run BEFORE any concatenation with `/`. The `<Link>` should receive `href="/programas"`, not `href="//s/en/nexa-paraguay/programas"`."}
